==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nook
<hw>Nook</hw> <pr>(n⟦oocr⟧k; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>nok</ets>; cf. Gael. & Ir. <ets>niuc</ets>.]</ety> <def>A narrow
place formed by an angle in bodies or between bodies; a corner; a
recess; a secluded retreat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How couldst thou find this dark, sequestered <qex>nook</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nook-shotten</ent>⟦br⟧
